{"response":"In the Hexagonal Architecture, a System Test is a type of test that focuses on the overall system architecture and its interactions. It provides an objective analysis to determine how well the system functions as intended.

A System Test can help identify issues related to the separation of concerns, modular design, and maintainability in your application's architecture. By testing the entire system from the perspective of different domains or interfaces, a Hexagonal Architecture helps developers understand how these components interact with each other and ensure they work together effectively.

In terms of methodology, you should conduct System Tests during the development lifecycle to verify that your application adheres to Hexagonal principles such as separation of concerns, modularity, and dependency on an external service. By performing comprehensive system tests, you can identify defects early in the development process and maintain high-quality code with proper integration and functionality verification.","userId":"test@test.com"}
